Denominator: N/A Indicator changes • This indicator now documents infants with a virological HIV test results returned. (MER v2.6.1 to 2.7): • Added new disaggregates to report on positive and negative infants with a negative or positive test result. • Updated guiding narrative questions. Reporting level: Facility Reporting Quarterly frequency: How to use: This indicator measures the number of HIV-exposed infants, with a test result returned in a reporting period, disaggregated by test outcome (positive or negative), age at sample collection, and ART initiation status. Identification is by virologic HIV testing: DNA PCR testing of dried blood spots (DBS) or whole-blood samples analyzed by high-throughput conventional or point of care (POC) platforms.
